                <note rend="inline" type="source">360M.1121 Devenis, Mikhail: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Steinhardt</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-05-09T17:00:00+03:00"
                            >May 9, 1941—5 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received May 9—4:55 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>938. The Embassy is today in receipt of a note from the Commissariat for Foreign
                    Affairs in reply to the Embassy’s most recent note of May 5, 1941 in the Devenis
                    matter stating that in its previous notes the Commissariat “gave an exhaustive
                    reply to the Embassy in the matter of Soviet citizenship of Mikhail
                    Devenis”.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Steinhardt</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
